scrap ~ , fuel { , missiles } , drones |

<event name="HEKTAR_COORDS_GET_1">
	<text>The Hektar employee goes to add your point, when he stops in surprise. "Huh? You actually reached 4 pointssss... Do you have brain damage? Why would you visssit sssso many sssstores. Eh, whatever. Congratulationssss. Here's the sssshiny key to the Hektar Mega-Market(tm). Ssssomething sssomething we waive all liability or whatever." Looks like they've sent some special coords for your Atlas. You can travel there during any sector jump before the Federation Capital.</text>
	<variable name="loc_uwupoint" op="add" val="1"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="HEKTAR_COORDS_GET_2"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="HEKTAR_COORDS_GET_2">
	<text>With that out of the way, now you can shop here.</text>
	<variable name="coords_hektar" op="set" val="1"/>
	<store>STORE_HEKTAR_DEFAULT</store>
	<choice>
		<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
		<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Do nothing.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>
-->

<mod:findName type = "event" name = "REVISIT">
<!-- <mod-append:choice req="coords_radikal" lvl="0" max_lvl="0" hidden="true" blue="true"> -->
 <mod-append:choice req="DJMOD_NO_COORDS_NO_VISIT_RADIKAL_SECTOR" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="true">
     <text>Construct a dummy to practice shooting in space, for 5~, and 1}.</text>
     <event load="TRYGET_COORDS_RADIKAL"/>
</mod-append:choice>
</mod:findName>

<event name="TRYGET_COORDS_RADIKAL">
	<text>You make the dummy and order your crew to take turns practicing their aim.</text>
	<item_modify>
		<item type="scrap" min="-5" max="-5"/>
		<item type="missiles" min="-1" max="-1"/>
	</item_modify>
	
	<choice>
		<text>They deserve some fun.</text>
		<event load="TRYGET_COORDS_RADIKAL_OUTCOMES"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<eventList name="TRYGET_COORDS_RADIKAL_OUTCOMES">
	<event load="GET_COORDS_RADIKAL"/>
	<!-- Total 1 / (1+1= 2) = 50% success -->
	<event load="NOTGET_COORDS_RADIKAL"/>
</eventList>

<event name="GET_COORDS_RADIKAL">
	<text>Suddenly, the dummy hits something small during an evasive maneuver, which you eventually find by calculating trajectories and carefully looking around since it's too small for detection.
	
	It's just a torn piece of clothing that probably belonged to someone who died near this beacon recently. There's a pocket.
	Inside, encased in frozen blood, is a data card that you don't take long to clean up and decrypt, containing FTL jump coordinates...</text>
	
	<variable name="coords_radikal" op="set" val="1"/>
	
	<choice>
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>The destination sector doesn't match anything in your database (which isn't reassuring) and is unlabeled (which isn't legal).
			
			The only clue is a logo with the letters "RK" on the back of the card.
			
			You will be able to reroute to it the next time you change sectors, knowing that showing up uninvited somewhere you don't know is always a risky move.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>We'll see.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="NOTGET_COORDS_RADIKAL">
	<text>Your crew enjoy the exercise, pretending they're using radical tactics to fight enemies. 
	At some point you think to yourself that there's probably a 50% chance anything special could have come out of this recreational activity...
	Then you call it a day and start focusing on your mission again.</text>
	<choice>
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>


